   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Eighty-seven THE PURIFYING OF THE CONSCIENCE</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>BY THE BLOOD Scripture: Heb 9:14 The function of the conscience God is the ruler of the universe, so He is also the ruler of man.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>God rules man by means of man s conscience.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>So in function, the conscience represents God to rule man.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Whatever is condemned by the conscience is also condemned by God.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The function of the blood God s righteousness causes God to condemn man; however, Christ bore man s sins and died for man, thus satisfying God s righteous requirement.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>In the sight of God, the blood of Jesus cleansed man from sin, thereby abolishing God s condemnation of man.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The purifying of the conscience by the blood As Jesus blood has cleansed man from sin in God s sight and has abolished God s condemnation of man, so it has also taken away the condemnation of man s conscience.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>By Jesus blood taking away the condemnation of man s conscience, man s conscience is purified so that there is no longer the feeling of shortcoming in the conscience.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The purifying of the conscience with its feeling causes man s conscience to be at peace before God.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The result</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>As the blood of the Lord Jesus cleanses man s conscience, it not only gives peace to man s conscience, but also enables man to serve God.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>How to partake of this cleansing</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Develop this point.</S>
   </TEXT>
